dict.string: mkdir -p ~/projects/{query} rm -rf ~/projects/active ln -s "~/projects/{query}" ~/projects/active echo "Active Project set to {query}"
Select a project to switch focus to, type * to see all.
rm -rf ~/projects/active && ln -s "{query}" ~/projects/active echo "Active Project set to {query}"

PROJECT="`ls -l ~/projects/ | grep active | sed 's,^.*projects/,,'`" /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -message "You're on $PROJECT. Click to view." -execute "open ~/projects/active"
source bash_functions rdef ~/projects/settings.yml browser echo "browser: {query}" >> ~/projects/settings.yml echo "Development Browser Set"
rm -rf ~/projects/active/links ln -s "{query}" ~/projects/active/links echo "Links Directory set to {query}"
rm -rf ~/projects/active/assets ln -s "{query}" ~/projects/active/assets echo "Assets Directory set to {query}"
rm -rf ~/projects/active/scripts ln -s "{query}" ~/projects/active/scripts echo "Scripts Directory set to {query}"
rm -rf ~/projects/active/theme ln -s "{query}" ~/projects/active/theme echo "Theme Directory set to {query}"
rm -rf ~/projects/active/files ln -s "{query}" ~/projects/active/files echo "Files Directory set to {query}"
source bash_functions rdef ~/projects/active/settings.yml notes echo "notes: {query}" >> ~/projects/active/settings.yml echo "Notes File set to {query}"
Find Assets in Active Project (Comps, Wireframes, etc)
Show SASS files in Active Project's Theme
Search for tpl.php files in site root
cd ~/projects/active/site-root && git pull && git push && /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -message "Git Push Done (after pulling)"
Git Push in Site Root (after pulling)
cd ~/projects/active/site-root && git pull && /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -message "Git Pull Done"
cd ~/projects/active/site-root /opt/local/bin/drush cc all && /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -message "Drupal Cache Cleared!" -title "Project Helper"
Launch Custom Shell Scripts for Active Project in Site Root. Hold CMD for Backgrounding.
Set dev URL, hold CMD for staging, option for production
Open files, folders, and URLs that have been set.
Set stuff to open at start

touch ~/projects/active/scripts/to-open.sh echo "open {query}" >> ~/projects/active/scripts/to-open.sh /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -subtitle "will open now" -message "Click to view current list to open" -execute "open ~/projects/active/scripts/to-open.sh"

cd ~/projects/active/theme sh ~/projects/active/scripts/start-theme.sh terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -subtitle "Theme Scripts Done" -message "Click to Edit" -execute "open -t ~/projects/scripts/start-theme.sh"

cd ~/projects/active/site-root sh ~/projects/active/scripts/start-site-root.sh terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -subtitle "Site Root Scripts Done" -message "Click to Edit" -execute "open -t ~/projects/active/scripts/start-site-root.sh"

open ~/projects/active/ open "`fdefonly ~/projects/active/settings.yml url-dev`" -a "`fdefonly ~/projects/settings.yml browser`" open "`fdefonly ~/projects/active/settings.yml url-staging`" -a "`fdefonly ~/projects/settings.yml browser`" sh ~/projects/active/scripts/to-open.sh /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -subtitle "Done opening" -message "Click to edit" -execute "open ~/projects/active/scripts/to-open.sh"
Search notes for 'Question: Answer' by passing in Question

QUESTION=$(echo {query} | sed "s/ /\.\*/") NOTES=$(cat ~/projects/active/settings.yml | grep ^notes: | sed "s/notes: //") ANSWER=$(cat "$NOTES" | grep "\w*:\s" | grep -i $QUESTION) echo $ANSWER echo $ANSWER | sed "s/.*: //" | pbcopy echo "Answer in clipboard"

## Suggested Utilities
If you install Terminal Notifier, the workflow can provide you with richer notifications.
gem install terminal-notifier
